--- 03 — Analyze trauma groups ---
  python scripts/02_behav_analyses/03_analyze_trauma_groups.py
================================================================================
TRAUMA GROUP ANALYSIS
================================================================================

This script performs:
  1. Hypothesis-driven grouping (LESS + IES-R cutoff)
  2. Hierarchical clustering analysis
  3. Behavioral validation of groups
Loaded 178 participants with complete trauma data
(excluded 0 participants with missing data)

================================================================================
HYPOTHESIS-DRIVEN GROUPING (LESS ENDORSEMENT + IES-R CUTOFF)
================================================================================

Criteria:
  - No Trauma Exposure: LESS = 0
  - Trauma - No Ongoing Impact: LESS ≥ 1 AND IES-R < 24
  - Trauma - Ongoing Impact: LESS ≥ 1 AND IES-R ≥ 24

Group Sizes:
  No Trauma: n=1
  Trauma - No Ongoing Impact: n=63
  Trauma - Ongoing Impact: n=114

Group Characteristics (Mean ± SD):

  No Trauma:
    LEC: 0.00 ± nan
    IES-R: 54.00 ± nan

  Trauma - No Ongoing Impact:
    LEC: 9.94 ± 3.39
    IES-R: 10.89 ± 7.34

  Trauma - Ongoing Impact:
    LEC: 10.17 ± 3.44
    IES-R: 43.81 ± 14.23

================================================================================
HIERARCHICAL CLUSTERING ANALYSIS
================================================================================

Features: LEC Total Events, IES-R Total Score
N participants: 178

Standardizing features (z-scores)...
  LEC mean=10.03, std=3.48
  IES-R mean=32.21, std=19.93

Computing hierarchical clustering with Ward linkage...

